        <definition>XXxvEthernet_Config * XXxvEthernet_LookupConfig</definition>
        <argsstring>(UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>XXxvEthernet_LookupConfig</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Looks up the device configuration based on the unique device ID/BaseAddress. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>A table contains the configuration info for each device in the system.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the base address of the device</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the configuration table entry corresponding to the given device ID/BaseAddress, or NULL if no match is found.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>In XSCT/classic flow, DeviceId is used to look up the device configuration. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
